Title : John McAnulty
Text : {{No footnotes|date = October 2015}}'''John McAnulty''' was a [[grain]] importer and an alleged informant from south [[County Armagh]], killed by the [[Provisional Irish Republican Army]] (IRA) .

McAnulty, a Catholic, was abducted by the IRA on 17 July 1989 in the [[Republic of Ireland]], tortured, and shot dead. His body was found the following day at [[Culloville]], South Armagh.

McAnulty was named at the [[Smithwick Tribunal]] as an intelligence source, and said to be involved in smuggling. He is said{{cn|date=October 2015}} to have informed the [[Royal Ulster Constabulary]]  that [[Garda Síochána]] Sergeant Owen Corrigan was colluding with the IRA, and that this led to his death.

